(527, 1, '2013-03-22 18:12:39', '2013-03-22 12:42:39', '<p style="text-align: justify;">We are looking for a web designer with expertise in CSS.</p>\r\n<h5>Who are we looking for?</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">You are someone who can write CSS for responsive sites and can read PHP code to be able to create html/css in Wordpress sites.</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Experience as a web designer: 0-5 years. Your role and profile will depend on the current comfort level with development and experience.</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Ability to mock up pages in Photoshop is desirable though not necessary.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>Remuneration and perks</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Salary offered is best in class. Expect a nice hike from your existing income.</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Laptop + Data cards are the norm for every member of the team. We also give each new joinee a fixed purse to do up their work space. Whether you buy ergonomic keyboards or your own personal mini fridge is totally your call :)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Web designer', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'web-designer', '', '', '2014-04-17 14:10:03', '2014-04-17 08:40:03', '', 0, 'http://www.ajency.in/?p=527', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(530, 1, '2013-03-22 18:18:27', '2013-03-22 12:48:27', '<p style="text-align: justify;">We are looking for mobile developers with expertise in iOS or Android app development. We make heavy use of frameworks like Sencha and Appcelerator Titanium for app development. </p>\r\n<h5>Who are we looking for?</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">You are someone who has worked on a minimum of 2 apps for modern devices like iOS and Android. </li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Experience on Sencha or Titanium helps.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h5>Remuneration and perks</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Salary offered is best in class. Expect a nice hike from your existing income.</li>\r\n<li style="text-align: justify;">Laptop + Data cards are the norm for every member of the team. We also give each new joinee a fixed purse to do up their work space. Whether you buy ergonomic keyboards or your own personal mini fridge is totally your call :)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', 'Mobile developers', '', 'draft', 'open', 'open', '', 'mobile-developers', '', '', '2014-04-17 14:09:53', '2014-04-17 08:39:53', '', 0, 'http://www.ajency.in/?p=530', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(543, 1, '2013-04-23 17:22:35', '2013-04-23 11:52:35', 'Paper will feature content from TED attendees, including blog posts and talk videos from the conference. Some TED Fellows, individuals who are selected by TED as partners, will provide exclusive content to Facebook throughout the week, which will also appear in Paper.\r\n\r\nThis marks the first time that Paper has collaborated with any outside group for content like this, or featured the same topic more than once in its Ideas section.\r\n<br><br>\r\n"When there are timely events where there''s something going on this week that really matters to a lot of people or may be really interesting to a lot of people, Paper sections can be a great way for them to get instantly connected to it," says Michael Reckhow, the Facebook product manager for Paper. "So for TED next week, we''re going to allow a lot of people to effectively experience a lot of the stuff that''s going on at TED, even if you''re not there, through Paper."\r\n\r\nThe Facebook-TED collaboration is a trial, according to a Facebook spokesperson. If things go well, it''s likely that Facebook will team with other organizations in the future, but there are not plans to do so at the moment.\r\nTED2014 begins Monday in Vancouver, Canada, and marks the conference''s 30th anniversary.\r\nThe two suspected pieces of debris are "reasonable in size," with the largest about 79 feet, according to Australian Maritime Safety Authority official John Young. "The objects are relatively indistinct on the imagery, but those who are experts say they''re credible sightings," Young said at a press conference.\r\n<br>\r\nHowever, Young warned that it will be very difficult to find the objects because of the size of the area, but said Australia will deploy every search effort at its disposal. He added that this area is already swirling with debris from ships and other maritime trash. However, search teams will continue to search for the objects until they find them, or conclud